text: Leonovsky () is a rural locality (a village) in Zarechensky Selsoviet, Kugarchinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 61 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 17 km from Mrakovo, 5 km from Voskresenskoye. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kugarchinsky District
title: Leonovsky
